tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a comprehensive visual overhaul,
  introducing a calming sleep-themed color palette, redesigning key layouts and
  UI components, and ensuring consistent styling across all sections to create a
  more polished and professional user experience.
overview: "The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app from a
  generic-looking application into a visually appealing and professional tool. I
  began by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas like the color
  palette, typography, spacing, and form elements as needing significant
  improvement. The approach involved a multi-step refinement process: first, a
  new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced in globals.css. Then,
  the main QuestionnaireForm and IntroSection were redesigned with decorative
  elements, improved progress indicators, and feature cards. Core UI components
  like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards were polished for a more
  modern feel. Finally, all 14 form sections and the ReportSection were
  systematically updated to ensure consistent application of the new styling,
  replacing old gray boxes with refined, themed card-style groupings. The
  outcome is an app with a cohesive, calming, and professional aesthetic,
  tailored specifically for a sleep health assessment."
